title: Nevermore
description: When a battle with Dr. Light pushes Raven over the edge, the Titans see a side of their friend they've never seen before: her temper. After Raven's creepy tantrum leaves Dr. Light begging for mercy, Beast Boy isn't quite sure how to treat her.

title: Mask
description: Slade sends a team of robotic commandos to steal a high-tech chip. The Titans stop the robbery but Starfire nearly gets hurt in the process. Robin becomes more determined than ever to find out who Slade is and what he's planning.

title: Snow Blind
description: While battling a mysterious creature in the wilds of Siberia, Starfire is lost in a blinding snowstorm. A reclusive young soldier named Red Star comes to her aid and the two become fast friends. When Robin and the rest of the Titans arrive, they discover Red Star hides not only a tragic past but a destructive secret.

title: Deep Six
description: When a mysterious villain makes off with dangerous toxic waste, the Teen Titans hop into the T-Sub and go on an undersea adventure to find out what is up and put a stop to it.

title: Go
description: How did Robin meet Starfire? What was Beast Boy's first joke? Why did Cyborg build his sonic cannon? When did Raven first call the Titans her friends? Return to the very beginning and see how it all started from the word go!

title: Troq
description: A brave hero from outer space called Val-Yor comes to Earth and asks for the Titans help in defeating an otherworldly menace known as The Locrix. But according to Val-Yor, Starfire may be the real problem.

title: Lightspeed
description: With Titans dispatched across the globe, members of the Hive Five figure they have it made. Unfortunately, their city-wide crime spree is cut short when a new hero in town spoils the fun. Handing him over to the Brotherhood of Evil may score the Hive Five points but actually catching this lightning-fast do-gooder is much harder than it seems.

title: Bunny Raven...or....How to Make a Titananimal Disappear
description: The Amazing Mumbo is up to his old tricks. And when the Titans try to stop the madcap, magician in mid-performance, Mumbo pulls a fast one. With a wave of his wand, he sucks the Titans into his hat, where our heroes discover a strange, magical world of weirdness. But in this world, Mumbo's holding all the cards. In a poof of magic, he changes the Titans into animals and takes away their powers. Can the Titanimals find their way out of the hat before Mubmo makes them disappear forever?

title: Aftershock Part 2
description: In a world without Titans, Slade has taken control of everything: the streets, the city and the heart of his young Apprentice. But are our heroes really gone?

title: The Prophecy
description: Why did Slade come back? What is he planning? Ever since the return of their arch-nemesis, the Titans have been searching for answers. But is there something Raven isn't telling them?

title: Spellbound
description: There's no one else quite like Raven: dark, somber and undeniably creepy. Even with four friends around her, Raven still manages to feel alone in Titans' Tower until she discovers a charming young wizard named Malchior trapped inside one of her ancient books. Raven finally finds someone who truly understands her. But will her relationship with Malchior threaten her friendship with the Titans?

title: Aftershock Part 1
description: A long lost friend of the Titans returns with a vengeance and Slade orders Overload, Cinderblock and Plasmus to launch a series of sinister attacks all over the city. Can our heroes stop three monsters, Slade and their newest enemies?

title: Things Change
description: After months of fighting the Brotherhood of Evil around the globe, the Teen Titans are finally back home. But a walk through the city reveals things are no longer as they remembered. And while Beast Boy wants everything to be just like it was in the past, he has to face the fact that in life things change.

title: Mother Mae-Eye
description: Every child needs a mother -- even five superpowered sweeties who live in a giant "T"

title: Car Trouble
description: Cyborg finished building the car of his dreams: the ultra-high-tech T-Car! Cyborg shows off his car to the Titans. Before Cyborg can take his car out for a spin, the Titans are called to a superstore where Overload is wreaking havoc.

title: Betrothed
description: The Teen Titans take a road trip to Starfire's home planet, Tamaran. But this is no ordinary visit. The Grand Ruler of Tamaran has arranged for Starfire to be married! The Titans try to go along with the strange ways of Starfire's homeworld. But Robin has a hard time believing Starfire really wants to marry someone she's never even met. And when he learns the Grand Ruler is none other than Blackfire, it seems like Starfire's evil sister may be up to her old tricks. Can Robin stop the wedding before it's too late?

title: Date with Destiny
description: Criminal Killer Moth threatens to destroy the city unless Robin takes his daughter Kitten to her junior prom. While the Titans are scouring the city in the search of Moth's hideout, Robin has no choice but to go along with the villain's demand.

title: The End Part 1
description: The stars are aligned. The sun is in eclipse. All of Slade's labors are about to reach fruition and the Titans are about to face their greatest challenge ever. But is there really any hope of preventing the end of the world?

title: Homecoming Part 2
description: The Doom Patrol has been saved but the sinister Brotherhood of Evil is still on the loose. It's just like old times for Beast Boy when he finds himself back on the team for one last mission to stop the Brotherhood once and for all no matter what the cost.

title: Forces of Nature
description: Dark Ominous clouds blow in from the East, bringing Thunder and Lightning with them: two forces of nature made flesh into the form of costumed super-teens. The stormy brothers aren't evil. They're just looking for a good time.

title: Wavelength
description: Brother Blood is back. And this time, it's personal. Cyborg learns Blood stole his blueprints and the villain is using Cyborg's technology to create a doomsday device. Can Cyborg take charge of the team and lead a mission to stop his arch-enemy? Or will he even get the chance?

title: Mad Mod
description: The Teen Titans awake to find themselves captured prisoners of Mad Mod. Miffed at the way the Titans disrespect their elders and interfere with the toils of hard working criminals, Mad Mod has decided to teach the teens a lesson.

title: Crash
description: When Beast Boy mistakes Cyborg's system recharger for a video game system, he accidentally infects it with a nasty computer virus. The virus quickly spreads to Cyborg himself causing the half-teen, half-machine to go haywire. And the only way to stop the virus is to shrink down to microscopic size and go on a fantastic voyage inside Cyborg. Does Amoeba Beast Boy have the brains to fix Cyborg's brains before a crazed Cyborg destroys the city?

title: Cyborg the Barbarian
description: Cyborg is mysteriously thrown into the distant past and lands in the middle of a barbarian village that needs his help. But with the nearest charging station 5,000 years in the future, Cyborg has no way to recharge and his power supply is dwindling. Can Cyborg get back to his own time before time runs out?

title: For Real
description: Control Freak returns to Titans' Tower with the ultimate Titans challenge, a series of events designed specifically to challenge the Teen Titans. But what happens to Control Freak's big plan when he finds himself facing not the real Titans but the Titans East?

title: Every Dog Has His Day
description: A green alien dog comes to Earth with a flying saucer chasing after it. When the alien dog bumps into green dog Beast Boy, the flying saucer abducts the wrong pooch. And when the Titans spot the alien dog, they mistakenly think it's Beast Boy!

title: Betrayal
description: After weeks as a Teen Titan, Terra has everything she ever wanted: a nice home, good friends and even a little romance with Beast Boy. Everything seems perfect but is it?

title: Revved Up
description: Robin's most prized possession is stolen by the hip hot-rodder Ding Dong Daddy. To get it back, they're going to have to beat him in a cross-country road race. But with Ding Dong Daddy making the rules and a few unexpected rivals joining in the competition, it's anyone's guess who will cross the finish line first!

title: Final Exam
description: The Hive Academy unveils its top graduates: Gizmo, Mammoth and Jinx. Before Slade will hire the new Hive Agents, he requires they pass one final exam: they must destroy the Teen Titans.

title: Stranded
description: An exciting battle on a distant space station ends with a tremendous explosion that blows the T-Ship apart and sends the Titans flying off in five different directions to crash land on a strange alien world. Will our five shipwrecked heroes ever be able to get back together and find their way home?

title: Calling All Titans
description: The final game has begun. While the Titans are spread throughout the globe on one last mission, Brotherhood mastermind, the Brain, makes his move. Robin has a strategy of his own but as all the villains begin taking down all the superheroes all at once, will it be enough to save his friends?

title: Deception
description: School's back in session at the Hive Academy and Gizmo, Jinx and Mammoth are up to something. To find out what, the Titans send Cyborg on a daring undercover mission to infiltrate the academy and blend in as one of their own. Using a holographic cloaking device, Cyborg creates the appearance he is fully human and takes on the persona of Stone, a tough transfer student who can change into a powerful creature of Solid Rock. But when the Academy's mysterious new headmaster, Brother Blood, takes an interest in Stone, will Cyborg's cover be blown?

title: Can I Keep Him
description: Starfire adopts a weird mutant silkworm named Silkie as a pet. But when she feeds him some alien food from Tamaran, Silkie has an unexpected and monstrous growth spurt. Can Starfire still keep her beloved worm?

title: How Long Is Forever?
description: A thief from the future called Warp travels back in time to steal an antique. When the Titans show up, the villain tries to escape. In an effort to catch the crook, Starfire is pulled into his Time Vortex and is hurled 20 years into the future.

title: Titan Rising
description: Terra returns to Titans' Tower and she's ready to join the team. After what happened to the last time they saw her, the Titans aren't sure that's such a good idea. Raven is positive it's not. Robin reminds her everyone deserves a second chance.

title: Episode 257-494
description: When Control Freak busts out of jail, throwing him back in should be as easy as clicking a remote. But after Control Freak hotwires some high-end AV equipment and escapes into a TV set, things get a little weird. Can the Titans make their way through the wacky world of television to catch the channel-flipping bad guy? Or will Control Freak make our heroes flip out?

title: Divide and Conquer
description: Cinderblock busts into prison and the Teen Titans show up to stop a jailbreak. But when Robin and Cyborg's big sonic boom maneuver goes awry, the bad guys get away and the boys blame each other.

title: Fear Itself
description: Raven doesn't do fear. Or at least, that's what she wants you to think. But when a ghostly, unknown force starts hunting down the Titans one by one, Titans' Tower turns into a house of horrors and even Raven gets rattled.

title: X
description: When the Titans track down the culprit in a string of recent robberies, our heroes are shocked to find themselves facing a foe they thought they'd never see again: Robin's evil alter ego, the mysterious Red X. Is Robin to blame for Red X's crimes?

title: Revolution
description: The Titans' Forth of July festivities are cut short when Mad Mod crashes the party declaring the American Revolution a Hoax and reclaiming the city for Jolly Old England. And if that wasn't enough, old Mod uses his high-tech cane to steal Robin's youth making King Moddie young again while Robin turns into a withered, dried-up old man. Can the remaining Teen Titans come up with a plan to take back their city and save their leader?

title: Titans East Part 2
description: Part two of the finale containing the final showdown between Cyborg and Brother Blood, and the creation of a new branch of the Titans' team. Titans East, a new tower in a new city with five new members: Aqualad, Bumblebee, Speedy and a pair of high-speed twins known as Mas y Menos.

title: Sisters
description: When an alien probe shows up to haul Starfire away, Starfire has no idea why it came. And when Starfire's sister, Blackfire, shows up to visit, Starfire just wishes she would leave. Blackfire's wild, cool and hip, everything Starfire's not.

title: Birthmark
description: Slade is back and this time he's after Raven. The question is why?

title: Switched
description: Starfire doesn't understand Raven's repression. Raven can't deal with Starfire's emotional outbursts. When Puppet King imprisons Robin, Cyborg and Beast Boy inside wooden puppets, the girls have to understand each other if they want to survive.

title: The End Part 2
description: The stars are aligned. The sun is in eclipse. All of Slade's labors are about to reach fruition and the Titans are about to face their greatest challenge ever. But is there really any hope of preventing the end of the world?

title: Transformation
description: The beautiful alien Starfire has never thought much about her looks. But when a strange red bump appears on her forehead, Starfire becomes concerned. Raven tells her not to worry. It's probably just a zit. Or is it?

title: The Sum of His Parts
description: A day of fun in the park is cut short when Cyborg suddenly freezes like a statue. His power cell is dying. While the problem is easily fixed with a new battery, Cyborg is reminded he's not completely human.

title: Terra
description: The Titans meet Terra. Gifted with earth-moving abilities, Terra can make rocks fly, mountains crumble and the ground tremble beneath her feet. It seems like she might make a great addition to the team. But Terra has a secret, a terrible secret.

title: Titans Together
description: All seems lost for young heroes across the globe. They have been spread far and wide, their lines of communication have been severed and one by one the Brotherhood of Evil takes them down. But as The Brain claims his victory is assured, one brave hero manages to slip thorough the Brotherhood of Evil's grasp: Beast Boy.

title: Apprentice Part 2
description: With no signs of Robin since Slade's Chronoton Detonator turned out to be a fake, the four remaining Teen Titans search the city for their missing leader. But their search is cut short when the Titan signal alerts them to a new villain in town. And when they arrive on the scene at a high-tech defense lab, they are shocked to discover this new villain is none other than Robin himself wearing a sinister new Slade insignia villain costume.

title: Kole
description: While in the Arctic Circle, the Teen Titans once again take on Dr. Light. And when an accident sends the Titans through the ice, they discover a new exotic Underworld and two new superheroes, Kole and her caveman sidekick Gnarrk.

title: The Quest
description: When Robin is defeated by the malicious martial artist, Kitarou, our hero decides if he wants to be the best, he needs more training. So he embarks on a difficult quest to seek a mysterious, legendary teacher known only as The True Master.

title: Employee of the Month
description: Beast Boy has only one real dream in life to someday, somehow own a moped. When Robin won't buy him one and Cyborg won't build him one, Beast Boy has only one way to make his dream come true. He has to get a job. But can vegetarian Beast Boy survive working at the Mega Meaty Meat fast food restaurant?

title: Only Human
description: When Cyborg was a fully human athlete, he loved trying to do more than he thought he could do. He always gave 110%. But now that his muscles are mechanical, Cyborg's limitations are built in. No matter how much he tries, 100% is all he's got.

title: Apprentice Part 1
description: Who is Slade? What is he planning? The questions keeping Robin awake at night are about to be answered. Slade contacts the Teen Titans and unveils his master plan: A Chronoton Detonator, a high-tech device has the ability to stop time forever.

title: Trust
description: The Brotherhood of Evil has begun its master plan to eliminate all of the young superheroes around the globe starting with honorary Titans Wildebeest and Hotspot. This new threat brings Robin to Morocco. But with an unknown enemy, how can anyone know who to trust?

title: Fractured
description: When Robin wrecks the R-Cycle while pursuing a thug named Johnny Rancid, he winds up with his arm in a cast and doubt in himself. He gets a helpful visit from his Number One Fan: a short weirdo from another dimension known as Larry the Titan!

title: The Beast Within
description: When Beast Boy begins turning into an angry aggressive Man Beast against his will, can the Titans save themselves from their savage friend?

title: Overdrive
description: Cyborg is a guy with a can do attitude. And with the new Maximum 7 processor upgrade driving his circuits, it looks like he can do more than ever before. But when Cyborg meets his multitasking match in the duplicitous Billy Numerous, can Cyborg really push himself to the max?

title: Titans East Part 1
description: Part one of the two-part finale containing the final showdown between Cyborg and Brother Blood and the creation of a new branch of the Titans' team. Titans East, a new tower in a new city with five new members: Aqualad, Bumblebee, Speedy and a pair of high-speed twins known as Mas y Menos.

title: Homecoming Part 1
description: When Beast Boy's former team, The Doom Patrol, is in trouble, the Titans must embark on a daring mission to save them. Beast Boy explains this can only mean one thing. The Doom Patrol's greatest foes are back. The Brotherhood of Evil has returned.

title: Winner Take All
description: Robin, Cyborg and Beast Boy are transported to an alternate dimension. There, the mysterious Master of Games invites our heroes and five other super-powered teens to participate in a competition: The Tournament of Heroes.

title: Haunted
description: Ever since the Titans' final confrontation with Slade, Robin has been haunted by one question: is Slade really gone? And when Cinderblock breaks out of jail, Robin finally gets his answer. He sees Slade. Robin goes after him fiercely determined to stop his nemesis once and for all. But when Robin learns Slade is planning to trigger a massive earthquake, it looks like there might be no stopping him this time. Will Robin stop Slade from destroying the city? Or is there more to Slade's plan than meets the eye?
